-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/brazil-s-aeris-energy-to-quadruple-wind-turbine-blade-production.html
Aeris Energy, the Brazilian maker of
blades for  wind turbines , will build a factory in the
northeastern city of Feira de Santana and double capacity of an
existing facility.  Aeris expects to begin construction on the 117 million-real
($56.9 million) Feira de Santana plant after it finds customers
for the blades, which will probably happen this year, Executive
Director Bruno Vilela Cunha said today in a telephone interview.  The company, based in Fortaleza, Brazil, will also boost
capacity of its existing factory in the northeastern city of
Pecem to 2,000 blades a year in 2015, from 1,000 now, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
